I hope to receive a letter from you this evening.\'a0 Willy says I must tell you he has been a good boy; but I don\'92t know that I can tell you the same; though he certainly is much better than he used to be.\'a0 I have not whipped him since you left. I suppose Columbia is as gay and lively as possible.\'a0 Susan is anxious for you to get her some Morocco, but I told her I knew you would not; you would think it was for me.\'a0 Write word if you \ul will\ulnone  get it.\'a0 If not she will commission Mr. H. Thompson, but she would rather you, as the last you got was so pretty.\'a0 I would like to know the \ul price\ulnone  of Rowlands Macassar, Kalydor, and Odonto, before you buy them.\'a0 If they are \ul reasonable\ulnone , I will wish them.\'a0 Your affectionate wife, Elizabeth F. Perry\
