ped here yesterday for a short time.\'a0 She seems well & I think more cheerful than she was.\'a0 Mamma was not well.\'a0 As I have literally \ul nothing\ulnone  to write you[.]\'a0 I might as well stop now, & Fanny is \ul crying\ulnone  for me.\'a0 She woke long ago, & Lindy has been holding her.\'a0 I hope to hear tonight.\'a0 Willie was so disappointed when I read to him what you wrote about Mr. Summer\'92s having no Dog to give him, that he had laid down on the rug, & cried; he thought Mr. Summer had treated him very badly, but do not mention this to Willie, as he does not like things told about him.\'a0 Your affectionate & \ul obedient\ulnone  Wife, Liz\
