Wednesday.
\f0\b0 \'a0 \
\
	The sun is shining bright today.\'a0 Tomorrow I will commence working in the garden.\'a0 Today Mary is to scour your Office & the Library.\'a0 I have moved Willie\'92s Cot into the large room, so the Library now can be kept in order.\'a0 I hope you are well, & doing the best for yourself.\'a0 I have no doubt if you do all that ought to be done, & try as hard as your opponent you will be \ul certainly\ulnone  elected.\'a0 If he is elected, it will be owing to your \ul inactivity\ulnone , inert\'85 &c but I leave this affair in your hands. Hoping you will prosper in it.\'a0 I will write by someone going to Pickens.\'a0 This is a delightful day.\'a0 Mrs. Walker sent me word today that I must go to the W\'85 Society, but I am too busy.\'a0\
