	The weather is still cold.\'a0 Russel Middleton used to be a particular friend of Mamma\'92s.\'a0 His Mother & his Aunt Mrs. Dehon were both intimate friends of Mamma\'92s.\'a0 We staid in the country at his Fathers once, & he was from a child \ul good\ulnone  & \ul pious\ulnone .\'a0 Mr. Hutson is some kind of cousin of ours, related to the Colcocks.\'a0 Mr. Burnett we knew at N. Haven, also Nat Heyward we knew there.\'a0 He & his mother are our cousins.\'a0 I am very sorry cousin Frederick Ford was defeated.\'a0 He is good & poor.\'a0 There is not a particle of news to tell you beyond Miss Lewis wedding.\'a0 I\'85, even the Mrs. Gowers, who Mrs. Arthur does not visit which makes it more accountable Susan\'92s not being; from this time we will all certainly have very little to do with them.\'a0 Christians so \ul calling\ulnone  \ul themselves \ulnone have certainly less of kindness, charity & love than any others, but they are \ul not\ulnone  \ul Christians\ulnone  & have no right to the cause.\'a0 Today I suppose you will speak, & I pray may have some effect & present your state\'85herself.\'a0 I hope your resolutions will be adopted.\'a0 E.F.P.\
