\fs29\fsmilli14667 \nosupersub .\'a0 That will be about Thursday.\'a0 Do you not wish to go to town to & hear her.\'a0 If I had known it, I would have proposed going down in the carri[a]ge to meet you in Columbia, & gone on with you to Charleston to hear her sing.\'a0 Mrs. Erwin Jones I hear is going down, will meet Mr. Jones in Columbia & go with him to Charleston to hear Jenny Lind,\'a0 They have money enough to do anything.\'a0 Do not speak of this to Mr. Jones.\'a0 I do not wish him to know that I think of her or mention her name for I despise her, & think her as malevolent & bad as ever be.\'a0 They are well matched.\'a0 Mr. Arthur has some as \ul bad\ulnone  \ul Christians\ulnone  in his church, as you can find anywhere, some who if they do not commit murder, are murderers in heart. Scott all today has been lying down.\'a0 He eats & drinks\'a0 but is too weak to stand well.\'a0 The stable is so small he hurts himself when he gets up, strikes against the stable.\'a0 You made a great mistake in hav[ing]\'a0 so little room for the horses.\'a0 I believe that is one reason they are lame & sick so constantly.\'a0 They did better in the old sable which was larger. You must not forget to buy the few things I have mentioned.\'a0 1 dollars worth of Hops, or fewer if you cannot bring so large a bundle.\'a0 Some Clover & Blue grass seed for Mamma, a bottle of Otto of Rose for Ann, 50 cts.\'a0 You got it at the confectioners I think.\'a0 Try & find my bundle that I have told you was to be sent to the Depository.\'a0 I am sorry you have said nothing of the writing desks I begged you to inquire the prices of for Mamma.\'a0 I would like you to have given me an answer.\'a0 I have not looked in the last papers, so I do not know the last news from Columbia, who were run for Governor even.\'a0 I was afraid I would see you spoken of as I would not like.\'a0 I thought as the majority agreed with you in wishing a Southern Congress, that you though you differed somewhat would on the whole please them.\'a0 I expect now you are more coldly treated as Dr. Lieber is, you ought to get those few who do agree with you, to do more for the Southern Patriot than merely take one copy.\'a0 They ought to take a dozen & help you sustain it at the commencement when it will need the exertions of every friend.\'a0 They ought to tally around you, come to your support.\'a0 Your attached [Wife], E.F.P.\
\'a0\
