	I will not finish, & only say once more, that I will be very thankful if your resolution for a Southern Convention is adopted, for the State will have something, & that is the \ul safest\ulnone  mode of\'85, but I doubt if they will be adopted, but I hope it will.\'a0Reuben has gone for a load of wood, & I hope by the time he returns Charles will be here to kill the hogs for it is very cold.\'a0 Charles is at Mr. Deans, & I am afraid from his not coming in, he is killing hogs for him instead, which will be very provoking.\'a0 I have sent Lindy to bring him in.\'a0 My pen needs mending.\'a0 I can hardly write.\'a0 My next shall be shorter & neater.\'a0 Lindy has just come back.\'a0 She met Charles coming in, so the hogs will be killed today.\'a0 Yours truly, E.F.P.\
