[December 1852]
\f0\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\fs32 \'a0
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\fs32 [Dear Anna]
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\fs32 \'a0
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\fs32 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 I do not know that I can get a cloak this winter.\'a0 I hope Aunt Mary\'92s can be changed.\'a0 If not I expect I will have to do without, as I cannot afford another, unless one could be got \ul reasonable\ulnone , so tell Eliza merely to let me know the prices.\'a0 I will then let her know.
\fs29\fsmilli14667  
\fs32 If she has not got the \ul second\ulnone  dress for Fanny, I expect one will be enough, for Aunt Mary\'92s bill is high.\'a0 Until I have paid for that, I find I must be economical.\'a0 Your dress I can have
\fs29\fsmilli14667  
\fs32 made here. & materials for a S\'85 for Fanny & a \ul pattern\ulnone  will be sufficient.
\fs29\fsmilli14667  
\fs32 You will be so well supplied with clothes you will need nothing next winter.\'a0If I had known Aunt Mary\'92s bonnet I could wear \ul at\ulnone  all I would not have sent for another, but it is \ul very\ulnone  \ul small\ulnone .\'a0 Next summer I will have a peice added between the \ul crown\ulnone  & \ul front\ulnone , & cover it over with ribbon & wear it as a summer bonnet, & make up for my extravagance in get[t]ing two, but the one Eliza has got will be very useful.
\fs29\fsmilli14667  
\fs32 Thank Aunt Eliza for her letter.\'a0 I write now in great haste, & when I have leisure I will write to her.\'a0 I am glad you pleased Mrs. O\'92Driscoll by your playing, & that your friends are satisfied & pleased with you.\'a0 I am sorry you have missed seeing so many.\'a0 The Spring is the pleasantest time for a visit. Tell Eliza I will not trouble her with shopping for a long time again, & when the Rail Road is finished I hope once in a while we can go down & shop for ourselves & not trouble our friends so often. The most economical way is not to send at all, but go without what we cannot get here, for when I once begin a list, I do not know where to end it.
\fs29\fsmilli14667  
\fs32 The weather is again bad.\'a0 You have had nearly 3 days together clear.\'a0 I am thankful that you have a happy contented disposition, & it is well , as you know in Greenville our happiness has to be found at home.\'a0 There is nothing beyond home to amuse & divert.\'a0 Everyone complains of the want of society, & the little sociability there is now, that there is less than there used to be.
\fs29\fsmilli14667  
\fs32 Give my love to \ul all\ulnone  my friends, particularly those in the house with you Mr. Elford ought to have been to see you.\'a0 I suppose he was busy.
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\fs32 \'a0
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

