\fs32 My dear Anna
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\fs32 \'a0
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\fs32 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 I am sorry you have such bad weather in Columbia.\'a0 You will find it duller than at home.\'a0 I hope you are behaving well.\'a0 You must write what purchases you make.\'a0 I sent the Book marks to Mary Mauldin & Mrs. Hopkins & they each sent word, they were very much pleased with them.\'a0 Mrs. Hopkins said she must look for something for you.\'a0 The pincushion Mrs. Hoke gave you & you intended giving to Aunt Harriet McCall, you had better not give to her, as it would be making a difference between her & your other Aunts, which would not be right.\'a0 You can give it to someone else, Sally Martin perhaps.\'a0 I would rather you get a Cloak, a \ul nice\ulnone  one to wear to \ul church\ulnone , in preference to anything else.\'a0 Get the \ul Cloak\ulnone  \ul first \ulnone & then what else you need afterwards.\'a0 Aunt Mary McCall wrote me word she had got a Cloak for herself in New York, where she was the past summer, & I have written to her to get me a Cloak.\'a0 Mr. McKay is going down next week & will bring it up. I hope you have given your Papa no trouble.\'a0 You must not interfere with his \ul business\ulnone .\'a0 Let him attend to \ul that\ulnone , even if you are left alone the whole day.\'a0 Tell Aunt Harriet when you see her, that I have not forgotten her Pincushion & needle\'85& as soon as I can get a pretty pattern will make them. Aunt Eliza wrote word that Mrs. Isaac Hayne & Eloisa Martin being in Columbia would make their social circle much smaller than usual, but there were many who would take a kind interest in you & she would carry you to see all of our friends.
\fs29\fsmilli14667  
\fs32 In a City you must remember persons are more particular than in the County, & as your good behaviour will reflect \ul credit\ulnone  on your \ul Parents\ulnone , you must keep that in mind & acquit yourself well.\'a0 I do not wish you to be grave & restrained.\'a0 Be \ul lively\ulnone  & \ul happy\ulnone , but be correct in all your words & actions.\'a0 As soon as you get down, have your patches cut out, so you can have some employment.\'a0 Aunt Mary or Aunt Eliza or Eliza or Sue will cut them for you.\'a0 Practice every day on the Piano.\'a0 Read your Prayer book & say your Prayers, \ul begin\ulnone  your day well, & it will be apt to \ul end\ulnone  well.
\fs29\fsmilli14667  
\fs32 I will now close.\'a0 Hext is asleep in the cradle.\'a0 Fanny is busy fixing something in the Entry.\'a0 Willie I expect is in the Library, & I do not know where Frank is.\'a0\'a0 Your affectionate Mother, E.F.P.
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

